================================================================================
WHEN A COMMERCIAL LICENCE IS NEEDED
================================================================================

Most users of Kaption do not need a commercial licence. AGPL-3.0 already
covers personal use, security research, AGPL-licensed forks, and
contributions back to the project.

You typically need a commercial licence only if one or more of the
following applies:

  1. You want to ship a closed-source product, application, or service
     that includes Kaption source code or substantial portions of it.

  2. You want to distribute a modified version of Kaption without
     releasing the modifications under AGPL-3.0.

  3. Your organisation has a policy that prohibits AGPL software in its
     products, even for internal tooling.

  4. You need a contractual warranty, indemnity, service-level
     agreement, or formal support that AGPL-3.0 does not provide.

  5. You want a written trademark licence to use the "Kaption" name or
     logo in a specific context (this is granted case-by-case and is
     not bundled by default).

